    <h1>Shapes</h1>

    <p>Back to <a href="./index.html">Specimens</a></p>

    <p>As for shapes, LibRext deals only with boxes. There are several options available for border radius, box shadow, widget heights, and card styles</p>

    <p>Border Radius -- A larger radius fits with larger boxes</p>

    <p>Box Shadow -- Larger sizes imply more distance between box layer and parent layer</p>

    <p>Widget Heights -- Presets for common/consistent UX elements. Like inputs, buttons, chips, etc.</p>

    <p>Card Styles -- Preset styles that combine several options mentioned above.</p>

    <h2>Border Radii</h2>

    <p>The system has six border radius styles:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>none</li>
      <li>xs</li>
      <li>sm</li>
      <li>md</li>
      <li>lg</li>
      <li>xl</li>
    </ul>


    <div class="shape-box-set border-radius">
      <% for(var i=0; i < borderRadiusSizes.length; i++) { %>
      <div class="shape-box-wrapper">
        <div class="shape-box b-radius <%= borderRadiusSizes[i].sizeCode %>"></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>

    <h2>Box Shadows</h2>

    <p>The system has five box shadow styles available:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>xs</li>
      <li>sm</li>
      <li>md</li>
      <li>lg</li>
      <li>xl</li>
    </ul>


    <div class="shape-box-set box-shadow">
      <% for(var i=0; i < boxShadowSizes.length; i++) { %>
      <div class="shape-box-wrapper">
        <div class="shape-box b-shadow <%= boxShadowSizes[i].sizeCode %>"></div>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>


    <h2>Widgets & Inputs</h2>

    <p>The system has five available widget heights:</p>

    <ul>
      <li>xs</li>
      <li>sm</li>
      <li>md</li>
      <li>lg</li>
      <li>xl</li>
    </ul>


    <div class="widget-set">
      <% for(var i=0; i < widgetSizes.length; i++) { %>
      <div class="widget <%= widgetSizes[i].sizeCode %>"></div>
      <% } %>
    </div>


    <h2>Cards</h2>

    <p>The system has five card styles available for use :</p>

    <ul>
      <li>xs</li>
      <li>sm</li>
      <li>md</li>
      <li>lg</li>
      <li>xl</li>
    </ul>

    <div class="cards-set">
      <% for(var i=0; i < cards.length; i++) { %>
      <div class="card <%= cards[i].sizeCode %>">
        <p><%= cards[i].specText %></p>
      </div>
      <% } %>
    </div>

